author: Courtenay Brown
title: Another 4.4 million filed for unemployment last week amid coronavirus crisis
description: Another 4.4 million Americans filed for unemployment last week, according to Labor Department data released Thursday. Why it matters: More than 26 million Americans have filed jobless claims in recent weeks as the coronavirus pandemic takes a never-before-see…
content:
More states moved toward reopening their economies following coronavirus lockdowns, as California's governor strengthened measures Wednesday. Coronavirus cases have surged past 842,600 and the death toll now exceeds 46,700, per Johns Hopkins.
